    <bioghist>
      <head>Biographical/Historical Information</head>
      <p>Finlay Forbes Ferguson was an architect and the descendant
         of a longtime Norfolk family</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
      <p>The collection principally consists of material relating to
         Ferguson's numerous descendents, including family trees, birth
         and death registers, correspondence, certificates, receipts,
         deeds, remembrances, newspaper clippings, and a diary and
         will. Also, consists of material, notably photographs,
         relating to Ferguson's involvement in the restoration of
         several of Hampton Roads' historic houses, including the
         Willoughby-Baylor House, the Moses Myers House, and the Adam
         Thoroughgood house. Of special note is correspondence
         concerning New York Life Insurance Company's payment of
         insurance claims after intercourse between the United States
         and Confederacy was declared unlawful in 1861.</p>
    </scopecontent>
